Nancy A. Roe is a community volunteer and Davis Citizen of the Year in 1987. Nancy graduated from Davis High School in 1960 and San Jose State in 1965. She has been involved in many UC Davis activities, including University Farm Circle and the UC Davis Foundation. Nancy has also been involved in many community activities including Davis Art Center, Yolo Family Service Agency, the Artery and the Pence Gallery. Nancy married Bill Roe in 1968, with whom she shared Davis Citizen of the Year honors. They have a son, Eric, and a daughter, Whitney.

